I"<p>In crypto talk, CBDC stands for <strong>central-bank-issued digital currencies</strong>, or simply <strong>central bank digital currencies</strong>.</p>

<p>The topic of CBDC became a hot topic in the blockchain and crypto community after the October 19th, 2020 annual meeting of International Monetary Fund where the FED chairman Jerome Powell had a talk on cryptocurrencies.</p>

<p>While most crypto enthusiasts do not give CBDCs a lot of credit, there are legitimate reasons for such assumption to be wrong.</p>

